President Obama expresses his gratitude to John Berry, who served as the Director of the Office of Personnel Management. Berry's contributions include streamlining the hiring process for federal employees, modernizing the workplace, promoting diversity within the federal workforce, and increasing the number of returning servicemembers hired by the government. The President considers Berry a champion for federal workers and acknowledges their important role in tasks such as border security, disease prevention, and public safety. Overall, President Obama believes that Berry's talent and dedication have made the country better off.